Copies files between two remote machines using different protocols(local, SCP, FTP or SFTP).

 Inputs\:
sourceHost - the host of the source file
sourcePort - The port for connecting to the source host
sourceUsername - the username for connecting to the host of the source file
sourcePassword - the password for connecting to the host of the source file
sourcePrivateKeyFile - absolute path of the private key file for public/private key authentication on the source host
sourcePath - the absolute path to the source file
destinationHost - the host of the destination file
destinationPort - the port for connecting to the destination host
sourceProtocol - the protocol used to copy from the source file
destinationUsername - the username for connecting to the host of the destination file
destinationPassword - the password for connecting to the host of the destination file
destinationPrivateKeyFile - absolute path of the private key file for public/private key authentication on the destination host
destinationPath - the absolute path to the destination file
destinationProtocol - the protocol used to copy to the destination file
fileType - the type of the file being copied

Responses\:
success - the file was copied successfully
failure - the file could not be copied

Result\:
The destination path where the file was copied
2ba37ee2-db03-4b69-87b4-825c6ccf484b.3d277a56-7fa3-4733-99f5-db47178f5f87.prompt=Enter privateKeyFile (for SSH)\: 2ba37ee2-db03-4b69-87b4-825c6ccf484b.3dbd8622-873c-4900-9607-5b7e100e0a6b.prompt=Enter a value for the protocol used to connect to the server 2ba37ee2-db03-4b69-87b4-825c6ccf484b.3dcbb0ad-6980-4347-a664-35e7e61b33a6.description=
Performs a mathematical operation on two numbers or strings

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.
operation - The operation to perform (+ - * ^ / > < \=\= \!\= >\= <\=).

Responses\:
success -  The operation completed successfully. If a boolean operation, it evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.

Returns\:
The raw result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Returns\:
Field 1 - The first value. Here for compatibility
Field 2 - The second value. Here for compatibility
Field 3 - The operation. Here for compatibility
formatted_result - The formatted result of the operation, for boolean values this is true or false.

Inputs\: coreHost – The name or ip of the SA core. coreUsername – The username for the SA core. corePassword – The password for the SA core. serverName – The name or ip of the server. serverUsername - The username for the server. serverPassword - The password for the server. Responses\: success – Successfully retrieved the list of agent installers. failure – The flow failed to retrieve the list of agent installers. NOTE\: This sample flow is created in order to be used as a subflow for Start Agent Install sample flow. 2ba37ee2-db03-4b69-87b4-825c6ccf484b.5823e2f8-f574-45dd-9a50-4c2b7f26cc21.prompt=Enter pty (for SSH)\: 2ba37ee2-db03-4b69-87b4-825c6ccf484b.65d1c59b-93a4-4f35-b3a5-c09434210804.prompt=Enter password\: 2ba37ee2-db03-4b69-87b4-825c6ccf484b.7d304e43-aa2e-456e-82f4-714b8e0f272a.prompt=Password 2ba37ee2-db03-4b69-87b4-825c6ccf484b.7dd32597-599d-4674-8714-aed7713fe344.description=
Runs a command and allows user to specify that it runs locally (in this case no port should be specified), via ssh, Global Shell, ROSH, Telnet, or RSH.

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
port - port number for connecting to the host
username - username to connect as
password - password
protocol - the protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local, WMI, NASConnectTelnet, or HPOM)
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete; increase its value if you are getting incomplete output results or timeout
command - the command to execute
arguments - the arguments to pass to the command
environment - specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running command
startDir - the path to the starting directory
pty - (true, false) whether to use pty
privateKeyFile - path to private key file, relative to ICONCLUDE_HOME
sasHost - the host we want to run the ROSH command on
sasHostUsername - the username used to run the ROSH command on sasHost
usernamePrompt - the prompt that when seen should send the username; used by the Telnet protocol; when used by the NASConnectTelnet protocol, the default value is 'NAS Login\:'
passwordPrompt - the prompt that when given should send the password; used by the Telnet protocol; when used by the NASConnectTelnet protocol, the default value is 'Password\:'
outputPath - network accessible path used by the operation to store temporary files. If not specified it points to \\host\admin$\temp\'. If this     path is not accessible you should change it to use another share that the host local system account has write access to. By default, the path will have to be  changed on Windows 2000 systems
nasDevice - The NAS device to run the command on when using the NASConnect protocol.
nasDeviceConsoleMode - The NAS device console mode used to run the command scripts that run the command on the given NAS device. If this input is empty, command scripts are not used, and the connection to the NAS device and the command are issued directly in the console; this is not recommended, since its error handling capabilities are limited and it might result in success even when the command fails to execute. The values for this input can be found in the NAS web interface, as a drop-down list when a new command script is created (ex. Cisco IOS enable).
hpomNode - Node on which the command is to be executed
hpomProtocol - Protocol to communicate with HPOM (http or https)

Responses\:
success - the command was executed successfully
failure - the command could not be executed

Extra Results\:
stdErr - the STDERR of the command
stdOut - the STDOUT of the command
